Item 2.06. Material Impairments.
On October 1, 2004, Anixter International Inc. (the "Company") announced a new branding name, Anixter Fasteners(SM) to its customers and vendors. The introduction of this brand name will result in Anixter recording an asset impairment charge of $1.8 million in the third quarter of 2004 to write-off the value assigned to the Pentacon name when that business was acquired by the Company. The Company's press release, dated October 6, 2004, is attached as Exhibit 99.1.
Item 9.01. Financial Statements and Exhibits.
99.1 Press Release, dated October 6, 2004, issued by Anixter International Inc.
