     On December 13, 2010, an arbitration panel in an arbitration brought by Raytheon Co. against Anixter Inc., a subsidiary of Anixter International Inc., entered an interim award against Anixter Inc. in the amount of $20.8 million. The arbitration is more fully described in Note 11 to Anixter International Inc.'s financial statements contained in its Quarterly Report on Form 10-Q for the quarterly period ended October 1, 2010. Raytheon may seek an additional award of attorneys' fees and arbitration proceeding costs in this matter, and the company may object to such a request. The company anticipates recording a pre-tax charge in the fourth quarter in an amount that approximates the award after consideration of insurance proceeds and all legal costs.
 
