     8.01 . Any of the following shall constitute an Event of Default:
Events of Default
     (a) . Any Borrower shall fail (i) to pay when due any principal of any Obligation, or (ii) to pay when due any interest on any Obligation, or any fee or other amount payable under this Agreement or any of the other Loan Documents and such failure under this clause (ii) shall continue for three (3) Business Days.
Failure to Make Payments When Due
