          (viii) . Promptly, from time to time, such other information, documents, records or reports relating to the Receivables or the condition or operations, financial or otherwise, of Seller as Buyer (or the Agent or any Managing Agent, as Buyer's assignees) may from time to time reasonably request in order to protect the interests of Buyer (and its assigns) under or as contemplated by this Agreement.
Other Information
          (b) . Seller will notify the Buyer (and the Agent and each Managing Agent, as Buyer's assignees) in writing of any of the following promptly upon learning of the occurrence thereof, describing the same and, if applicable, the steps being taken with respect thereto:
Notices
          (i) . The occurrence of each Amortization Event and each Potential Amortization Event, by a statement of an Authorized Officer of Seller.
