          (ii) . (A) The entry of any judgment or decree against Seller or any of its Subsidiaries if the aggregate amount of all judgments and decrees then outstanding against Seller and its Subsidiaries exceeds $25,000,000, or (B) the institution of any litigation, arbitration proceeding or governmental proceeding against Seller, which individually or in the aggregate could reasonably be expected to have a Material Adverse Effect, or which seeks to enjoin performance of or otherwise relates to the Transaction Documents.
Judgment and Proceedings
 
          (iii) . The occurrence of any event or condition that has, or could reasonably be expected to have, a Material Adverse Effect.
